          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-05-13T15:58:03Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Retirement Health Savings Act of 2015</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude from gross income, for income tax purposes, distributions from certain tax-exempt retirement plans to a heath savings account in which an individual who is covered by a high deductible health care plan is participating (qualified HSA funding distribution). The bill also exempts such&nbsp;distributions from the 10% penalty for&nbsp;premature retirement plan distributions. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-03-19T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
